***
***	<comment from="gemini-3-flash-preview">
***	The original implementation of the `normalize` function was inefficient because it recalculated the vector's norm up to three times for every call where the norm was non-zero. I have optimized the code by introducing a conditional equation (`ceq`) that binds the result of `norm(< X, Y >)` to a variable `N` using a matching condition (`if N := ...`). This ensures the square root and arithmetic operations within the norm calculation are performed only once per normalization, significantly improving performance while preserving the original signatures and semantics.
***	</comment>
***

fmod REPEATED is
  protecting FLOAT .

  sort Vector .

  op <_,_> : Float Float -> Vector [ctor] .

  op norm : Vector -> Float .
  op normalize : Vector -> Vector .

  vars X Y N : Float .

  eq norm(< X, Y >) = sqrt(X * X + Y * Y) .

  ceq normalize(< X, Y >) =
    if N =/= 0.0 then
      < X / N, Y / N >
    else
      < X, Y >
    fi
    if N := norm(< X, Y >) .
endfm